WEBVTT

00:04.090 --> 00:07.326
Wow. They found a way to make
the human being even creepier.

00:07.360 --> 00:08.693
Covering him in icicles.

00:08.712 --> 00:10.129
I think it's festive.

00:10.163 --> 00:11.714
Yeah, my favorite
Christmas tradition

00:11.748 --> 00:13.332
is trimming the hellraiser.

00:13.366 --> 00:15.184
Guys, I found something
we can watch together

00:15.218 --> 00:16.752
for Christmas this year.

00:16.803 --> 00:20.272
The long-lost 1981 <i>Inspector
Spacetime Holiday Special.</i>

00:20.307 --> 00:22.608
Run time two and half hours
and so critically reviled

00:22.642 --> 00:25.127
that after it aired, the creator
has his knighthood revoked.

00:25.161 --> 00:26.612
That sounds terrible.

00:26.646 --> 00:28.247
I want to watch it twice,

00:28.281 --> 00:30.249
but I'm spending Christmas
with my relatives.

00:30.283 --> 00:33.118
Or rather, I'm spending
the day with my relatives

00:33.153 --> 00:34.770
while they refuse
to acknowledge Christmas.

00:34.821 --> 00:37.556
You Jehovah's Witnesses--
so severe.

00:37.590 --> 00:39.558
Andre and I will be spending
Christmas giving gifts

00:39.592 --> 00:41.493
to the more persuadable
of our Jewish friends.

00:41.528 --> 00:43.946
I wouldn't call an unannounced
visit from your pastor "a gift."

00:43.997 --> 00:45.397
And don't bother this year.

00:45.415 --> 00:46.949
I'll be at the movies
with my bubbe.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.468
You're not taking both of them?

00:49.502 --> 00:51.470
Well, one's dead.

00:51.504 --> 00:52.788
- What?
- I was looking forward

00:52.839 --> 00:54.590
to hanging out with you guys
this Christmas.

00:54.624 --> 00:56.709
This semester has been so long
and dark and angry.

00:56.743 --> 00:57.743
I was thinking we could have

00:57.777 --> 00:59.044
some light-hearted fun
as a family.

00:59.079 --> 01:00.212
I think what we've learned,
Abed,

01:00.246 --> 01:02.514
is that attempts to make
the holidays brighter

01:02.549 --> 01:04.183
tend to give them
a certain darkness.

01:04.217 --> 01:05.718
Oh, I don't know
if I agree with that.

01:05.752 --> 01:07.853
♪ Deck the halls
with boughs of holly ♪

01:07.887 --> 01:08.854
Actually, maybe I do.

01:10.757 --> 01:12.591
♪ 'tis the season
to be jolly ♪

01:12.609 --> 01:14.860
♪ fa la la la la
la la rock on! ♪

01:14.894 --> 01:16.862
Merry Christmas, Greendale.

01:16.896 --> 01:18.731
Glee club here, reminding you

01:18.765 --> 01:21.283
that our Christmas pageant
is coming.

01:21.317 --> 01:23.635
Next stop, regionals!

01:23.670 --> 01:24.620
What the hell
are "regionals?"

01:24.654 --> 01:26.372
They never stop talking
about it.

01:26.406 --> 01:28.707
♪ I said deck ♪

01:28.742 --> 01:30.709
Please tell me we were
not this obnoxious

01:30.744 --> 01:31.910
the year we filled in for them.

01:31.945 --> 01:33.812
T-minus five seconds
till hip-hop remix.

01:33.847 --> 01:35.297
Four, three.

01:35.331 --> 01:37.833
Come on!
Re-re-re-remix!

01:37.884 --> 01:39.785
Re-re-re-remix!

01:39.803 --> 01:40.886
♪ Fa la la la la
f-a l-a ♪

01:40.920 --> 01:41.887
♪ come on whoo ♪

01:41.921 --> 01:43.288
You're awfully quiet, Jeff.

01:43.323 --> 01:45.290
Nobody hates Glee Club
more than you.

01:45.325 --> 01:47.643
Today I'm just content
to sit back and enjoy the show.

01:47.677 --> 01:49.628
And now
our pop music mash-up!

01:49.662 --> 01:51.296
Elton Lil' John Lennon!

01:51.314 --> 01:52.297
Kick it!

01:52.315 --> 01:53.899
Hey, tiny dancer!

01:53.933 --> 01:55.150
Okay!

01:55.185 --> 01:56.402
Stop!

01:56.436 --> 02:00.239
Cease and desist.

02:00.273 --> 02:02.274
Glee club, meet ASCAP,

02:02.308 --> 02:05.411
protecting musical copyrights
since 1914.

02:05.445 --> 02:06.745
It appears they have received
an anonymous tip

02:06.780 --> 02:09.031
that unlicensed material
was being performed here

02:09.082 --> 02:10.582
without the artists' permission.

02:10.616 --> 02:12.167
Merry Christmas, everyone.

02:12.202 --> 02:14.253
Glee club
just became History Club.

02:16.000 --> 02:22.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:24.831 --> 02:26.298
My soul is dead!

02:26.332 --> 02:27.866
Oh!

02:27.901 --> 02:30.436
Okay, if anyone asks,
we were never here.

02:33.339 --> 02:34.840
Why?

02:34.858 --> 02:38.861
♪ Give me some rope,
time in a tree ♪

02:38.895 --> 02:42.064
♪ give me the hope
to run out of steam ♪

02:42.115 --> 02:45.451
♪ somebody said
we could be here ♪

02:45.485 --> 02:49.404
♪ we could be roped up,
tied up, dead in a year ♪

02:49.456 --> 02:54.460
♪ I can't count the reasons
I should stay ♪

02:54.494 --> 02:58.800
♪ one by one they all
just fade away ♪

02:58.801 --> 03:01.401
Sync by honeybunny, corrected by susanaLC
www.addic7ed.com

03:01.584 --> 03:03.769
The Glee Club
is at Westside Hospital,

03:03.803 --> 03:07.105
recuperating from
a collective nervous breakdown.

03:07.140 --> 03:10.676
This is the second glee club
we've lost in two years.

03:10.710 --> 03:13.211
We might have to cancel
the Christmas pageant.

03:13.229 --> 03:16.064
And to think they were
this close to regionals.

03:16.099 --> 03:17.115
What the hell are regionals?

03:17.150 --> 03:19.568
They're this close, Pierce.

03:19.602 --> 03:22.554
Anyway, an old friend
wants to talk to you.

03:22.572 --> 03:24.790
Your favorite
glee club instructor,

03:24.824 --> 03:28.777
the dreamy and boyish
Mr. Cory Radison!

03:28.828 --> 03:30.662
Oh!

03:30.697 --> 03:33.282
Uh, I thought I told you
to call me Mr. Rad.

03:33.333 --> 03:34.466
Or Cory.

03:34.501 --> 03:35.918
Just don't call me
"late to dinner."

03:35.952 --> 03:37.452
Unless you're serving
brussels sprouts!

03:37.504 --> 03:40.589
I won't, I promise!

03:40.623 --> 03:43.041
This guy's like human froyo.

03:43.076 --> 03:45.878
Look, when the last glee club
died in that bus crash,

03:45.912 --> 03:47.246
you guys stepped up.

03:47.280 --> 03:49.765
And you were the best gosh darn
emergency substitutes

03:49.799 --> 03:50.766
I've ever worked with.

03:50.800 --> 03:52.301
- Aw!
- Well, this time...

03:52.352 --> 03:55.304
I'm not gonna kid you.
I won't be easy.

03:55.355 --> 03:56.655
- Oh!
- Your best...

03:56.689 --> 03:58.490
Won't be good enough.

03:58.525 --> 04:00.959
And ten times your best
will be so bad,

04:00.994 --> 04:03.028
I will yell at you.

04:03.062 --> 04:05.864
But I promise,
if we dig down--

04:05.899 --> 04:07.866
- Pass.
- Yeah.

04:07.901 --> 04:11.203
Okay.

04:11.237 --> 04:13.505
Whew.

04:13.540 --> 04:16.507
Don't you hurt him.

04:16.543 --> 04:17.875
Mr. Rad!

04:17.911 --> 04:19.995
I feel like we let
Mr. Rad down.

04:20.046 --> 04:22.014
No, he let himself down
when he left the house

04:22.048 --> 04:23.582
this morning
wearing a sweater-vest.

04:23.616 --> 04:25.334
I guess we did have fun
last time.

04:25.385 --> 04:27.219
Did we?
I can hardly remember.

04:27.253 --> 04:29.137
It's all a weird, happy,
musical fog.

04:29.172 --> 04:31.023
Yeah, it was almost
like being on ecstasy,

04:31.057 --> 04:33.091
only instead of having
pointless conversations

04:33.125 --> 04:35.177
and dancing like idiots--
wait.

04:35.228 --> 04:37.679
It was exactly
like being on ecstasy!

04:37.730 --> 04:38.864
That's what worries me
about this guy.

04:38.898 --> 04:41.183
He is equal parts hanson
and manson.

04:41.234 --> 04:44.169
Nobody let him corner you until
he is out of recruitment mode,

04:44.203 --> 04:45.604
or next thing you know,

04:45.638 --> 04:48.340
we'll all be caring
about Christmas pageants and...

04:48.374 --> 04:49.324
Regionals.

04:49.359 --> 04:50.359
- You're right, deal.
- Ugh.

04:50.410 --> 04:51.360
- Agreed.
- Got you.

04:51.411 --> 04:53.078
What the hell are regionals?

05:02.538 --> 05:03.922
What are you still doing here?

05:03.957 --> 05:05.791
I thought I'd give her
one more tinkle

05:05.825 --> 05:07.960
before I took down decorations.

05:07.994 --> 05:10.662
No glee club means no pageant,
means no Christmas.

05:10.697 --> 05:12.030
I'm sure trying
to make things brighter

05:12.065 --> 05:13.966
just would've made
more darkness.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.402
That sounds like
a certain ex-lawyer talking.

05:17.437 --> 05:19.771
I see a lot of myself in you,
Abed.

05:19.806 --> 05:21.673
You care about your friends,
and you wish they cared

05:21.708 --> 05:23.108
more about each other.

05:23.142 --> 05:25.394
That's not an easy position
to be in sometimes.

05:25.445 --> 05:26.478
I just want my friends and I

05:26.512 --> 05:27.679
to have
a merry Christmas together.

05:27.714 --> 05:29.214
Well, maybe you could start

05:29.248 --> 05:31.950
by giving them the greatest
Christmas gift of all.

05:31.985 --> 05:33.385
What's that?

05:33.419 --> 05:34.519
Glee!

05:34.554 --> 05:36.688
♪ It's a feeling you get ♪

05:36.723 --> 05:39.958
♪ when your brain finally lets
your heart get in its pants ♪

05:39.993 --> 05:41.159
♪ Glee! ♪

05:41.194 --> 05:42.461
♪ It's like a drug
that you use ♪

05:42.495 --> 05:44.046
♪ that turns pain into shoes ♪

05:44.080 --> 05:46.164
♪ and your shoes into dance ♪

05:46.198 --> 05:49.217
♪ How's your piano
still playing this song? ♪

05:49.252 --> 05:50.502
♪ Glee is the answer ♪

05:50.536 --> 05:52.437
♪ when questions are wrong ♪

05:52.472 --> 05:55.257
♪ You'll understand
if you just sing along ♪

05:55.308 --> 05:56.758
♪ 'cause glee is the gift ♪

05:56.809 --> 06:00.228
♪ that you need ♪

06:00.263 --> 06:02.898
♪ Glee is what I'll spread
to my friends ♪

06:02.932 --> 06:07.019
♪ like a virus that sends them
to a healthier place ♪

06:07.053 --> 06:09.271
♪ Glee!
I'll understand every scene ♪

06:09.322 --> 06:11.156
♪ because they'll sing
what they mean ♪

06:11.190 --> 06:12.824
♪ instead of making a face ♪

06:12.859 --> 06:16.227
♪ Families are closer
when families are winning ♪

06:16.245 --> 06:19.247
♪ Everything's cooler
when cameras are spinning ♪

06:19.282 --> 06:21.466
♪ singing and dancing
in unison... ♪

06:21.501 --> 06:22.617
♪ in-inning ♪

06:22.669 --> 06:24.920
♪ Glee is the gift ♪

06:24.954 --> 06:27.472
♪ that we need ♪

06:27.507 --> 06:29.441
Glee!

06:29.475 --> 06:31.009
Thank you, Mr. Rad.

06:31.044 --> 06:32.477
Don't break down the set yet.

06:32.512 --> 06:36.298
I'm gonna try to get my friends
to be in the Christmas pageant.

06:36.349 --> 06:40.619
Thank you, Abed!

06:40.653 --> 06:42.154
Thank you.

06:52.026 --> 06:53.076
Merry Christmas, Troy.

06:53.110 --> 06:54.828
Abed, you look gleeful.

06:54.862 --> 06:56.496
Troy, don't you think
it might actually be fun,

06:56.530 --> 06:58.031
doing this Christmas pageant
for the glee club?

06:58.065 --> 07:00.300
Abed, we hate the glee club.

07:00.334 --> 07:01.735
Yeah.

07:01.769 --> 07:03.136
I guess I just like
liking things.

07:03.170 --> 07:06.039
Abed.

07:06.073 --> 07:09.626
Look, you know I'd do anything
you did, but...

07:09.677 --> 07:11.177
I'm a Jehovah's Witness.

07:11.212 --> 07:12.679
We're not supposed
to celebrate Christmas.

07:12.713 --> 07:14.948
I've been thinking about that.

07:14.982 --> 07:16.800
I may have a loophole.

07:16.851 --> 07:18.351
What if you were
a Jehovah's Witness

07:18.385 --> 07:20.804
that was merely pretending
to be into Christmas,

07:20.855 --> 07:22.222
gathering clues and blending in

07:22.256 --> 07:23.923
to take down the holidays
from within?

07:23.958 --> 07:26.259
You mean like a spy
investigating,

07:26.293 --> 07:27.861
making it seem
like I'm celebrating,

07:27.895 --> 07:31.197
when actually I'm infiltrating
Santa's operation?

07:31.232 --> 07:32.198
- Yoip!
- ♪ Going deep cover ♪

07:32.233 --> 07:33.616
♪ past enemy lines ♪

07:33.651 --> 07:35.285
♪ making everybody think
I'm on the Christmas side ♪

07:35.319 --> 07:37.303
♪ rocking warm sweaters,
hanging big-ass lights ♪

07:37.338 --> 07:39.205
♪ if the fat man can see me,
yo it's gotta look right ♪

07:39.240 --> 07:40.824
♪ I'll watch all the tv specials
that I never could ♪

07:40.875 --> 07:42.942
♪ I'll even cry during the sad
ones, like James Bond would ♪

07:42.977 --> 07:44.744
♪ and when the big night comes,
it's time to set the bait ♪

07:44.778 --> 07:46.629
♪ cold milk, hot cookies ♪
♪ decorative plate ♪

07:46.664 --> 07:47.714
♪ And he'll come down
the chim-in-ey ♪

07:47.748 --> 07:48.948
♪ and it will be
just him and me ♪

07:48.966 --> 07:50.283
♪ But he won't know
we're enemies ♪

07:50.317 --> 07:51.501
♪ 'cause I'll play sincere,
spring a trap ♪

07:51.552 --> 07:52.802
♪ like that, hug him tight,
get on his lap ♪

07:52.837 --> 07:54.287
♪ and tell him he can
come back every year ♪

07:54.321 --> 07:55.972
♪ 'cause I am Jehovah's
most secret witness ♪

07:56.006 --> 07:57.841
♪ so I might have to dedicate
my life to Christmas ♪

07:57.892 --> 08:01.327
♪ and act just like I love it
till the day I die ♪

08:01.362 --> 08:03.513
♪ a-b-e-d
connoisseur of Christmas ♪

08:03.564 --> 08:05.598
♪ on the spectrum,
none of your business ♪

08:05.632 --> 08:07.233
♪ talks to fast to comprehend ♪

08:07.268 --> 08:08.768
♪ just wanna do right
by my friend ♪

08:08.803 --> 08:11.137
♪ if years were seasons,
this December ♪

08:11.172 --> 08:13.139
♪ would be the December
of our December ♪

08:13.157 --> 08:14.807
♪ more blueprints
than Howard Hughes ♪

08:14.825 --> 08:16.776
♪ but if they are blue prints,
how do we choose? ♪

08:16.810 --> 08:18.344
♪ we have to be happy
to get to the end ♪

08:18.379 --> 08:20.446
♪ we have to save Christmas
to save our friends ♪

08:20.480 --> 08:22.348
♪ we have to save
Christmas to save our friends ♪

08:22.383 --> 08:24.918
♪ we have to save Christmas
to save our friends ♪

08:24.952 --> 08:26.819
Hey, guys.

08:26.837 --> 08:28.054
Rapping?

08:28.088 --> 08:31.391
- Yep, wanna join us?
- Totally!

08:31.425 --> 08:33.993
Wait, you guys never
let me rap with you.

08:34.028 --> 08:35.128
Well, we're gonna need
all hands on deck

08:35.162 --> 08:38.131
if we're gonna go to regionals.

08:38.164 --> 08:39.631
Cool.

08:39.667 --> 08:41.568
I just need to...
Study...

08:41.602 --> 08:43.369
Though...In my room.

08:43.404 --> 08:44.804
So have fun!

08:44.838 --> 08:46.472
And then, this morning,

08:46.506 --> 08:47.640
I could hear them
in the bathroom,

08:47.674 --> 08:49.742
doing
country Western mash-ups.

08:49.777 --> 08:51.544
And they won't stop talking
about regionals!

08:51.579 --> 08:52.812
Maybe it's nothing.

08:52.846 --> 08:54.147
Yeah, if "nothing"
wears a sweater-vest

08:54.181 --> 08:55.698
and seems aggressively asexual.

08:55.733 --> 08:58.351
Come on, let's all study
for our biology final

08:58.385 --> 09:00.069
in our old--

09:00.120 --> 09:02.088
Where's our table?

09:02.122 --> 09:04.891
Who's that guy?

09:04.925 --> 09:06.793
You guys all see him too,
right?

09:06.827 --> 09:08.378
- Hey, guys.
- Merry Christmas, y'all.

09:08.429 --> 09:10.046
Sorry about the rearrangement.

09:10.097 --> 09:11.798
We need this space to rehearse
for the pageant.

09:11.832 --> 09:13.666
But we're not doing
the pageant.

09:13.684 --> 09:15.435
Look, guys,
I hear your negativity,

09:15.469 --> 09:17.203
but also,
can I counter with this?

09:17.238 --> 09:19.005
Who hates glee?

09:19.039 --> 09:20.807
Listen to how that sounds.

09:20.841 --> 09:23.176
Glee literally
means "glee."

09:23.210 --> 09:24.477
Oh, stop it!

09:24.511 --> 09:26.396
Not liking glee club
doesn't make us bullies,

09:26.447 --> 09:28.548
and implying that
is reverse bullying.

09:28.582 --> 09:29.916
Good point.
Sing about it?

09:29.950 --> 09:30.917
No!

09:30.951 --> 09:33.253
I understand them,
but you, Pierce?

09:33.287 --> 09:34.754
Your generation invented music!

09:34.788 --> 09:37.624
I don't know
about "invented."

09:37.658 --> 09:39.692
- Perfected, maybe.
- Pierce!

09:39.710 --> 09:41.561
They're just trying to pander
to your demographics'

09:41.595 --> 09:43.796
well-documented
historical vanity. Resist!

09:43.831 --> 09:45.632
Abed,
wasn't Santa Claus himself

09:45.666 --> 09:46.966
part of Pierce's peer group?

09:47.001 --> 09:49.002
I believe so.

09:49.036 --> 09:51.037
One, two,
three, four.

09:51.055 --> 09:53.539
♪ Santa Claus
was born in 1945 ♪

09:53.557 --> 09:56.476
♪ He had a boogie woogie
Coca-Cola army jive ♪

09:56.510 --> 09:59.596
♪ and when the commies
gave the polio to Doris Day ♪

09:59.647 --> 10:01.648
♪ Santa helped the Beatles
chase McCarthy away ♪

10:01.682 --> 10:04.651
♪ that baby boomer Santa ♪

10:04.685 --> 10:06.436
♪ he's never gonna die ♪

10:06.487 --> 10:10.406
♪ Santa fought at Woodstock
and Vietnam ♪

10:10.441 --> 10:15.128
♪ and smoked a ton of acid
and burnt his bra ♪

10:15.162 --> 10:19.582
♪ and then in 1970,
he did more drugs ♪

10:19.617 --> 10:22.635
♪ and his hair stayed long
and he ♪

10:22.670 --> 10:25.038
♪ grew a mustache ♪

10:25.072 --> 10:27.740
♪ baby boomer Santa ♪

10:27.758 --> 10:32.128
♪ he's gonna stay
Ali-I-I-ive ♪

10:32.179 --> 10:36.916
♪ Santa invented
Spielberg and microchips ♪

10:36.934 --> 10:41.587
♪ Santa invented
Coca-Cola and aerobics ♪

10:41.622 --> 10:44.924
♪ he made the iron curtain
and the <i>Gremlins 2 ♪</i>

10:44.942 --> 10:48.144
♪ fake butter and AIDS
and <i>Twin Peaks! ♪</i>

10:48.195 --> 10:50.029
♪ Baby boomer Santa ♪

10:50.064 --> 10:51.814
♪ thank you for MTV ♪

10:51.865 --> 10:54.867
♪ Ow! Ow! ♪

10:54.902 --> 10:56.452
♪ Baby boomer Santa ♪

10:56.487 --> 10:58.821
♪ thank you for everything ♪

10:58.872 --> 11:00.573
♪ you're welcome ♪

11:00.607 --> 11:03.710
♪ you're welcome
for everything ♪

11:03.744 --> 11:05.211
♪ in the world ♪

11:05.245 --> 11:06.879
♪ you're welcome ♪

11:06.914 --> 11:10.049
♪ you're welcome
for all that I bring ♪

11:10.084 --> 11:11.651
♪ to the world ♪

11:11.685 --> 11:14.120
♪ I'm baby boomer Santa ♪

11:14.138 --> 11:18.791
♪ I bring the gift
of the world ♪

11:18.809 --> 11:20.727
♪ baby boomer Santa ♪

11:20.761 --> 11:25.014
♪ I'm an American pearl ♪

11:25.065 --> 11:27.233
- Pierce is on board.
- That's great!

11:27.267 --> 11:28.634
For the Christmas queen,
I'm hoping

11:28.652 --> 11:29.969
we can get Shirley or Annie.

11:30.004 --> 11:31.404
They both have
really strong voices

11:31.438 --> 11:33.323
and natural
♪ vibrato. ♪

11:33.357 --> 11:36.042
- There's also Britta.
- Britta's adorable!

11:36.076 --> 11:38.328
So Shirley or Annie
for the Christmas queen.

11:38.362 --> 11:39.662
There's a leaf
on Britta's head.

11:39.697 --> 11:41.414
She's playing a tree!

11:41.448 --> 11:43.883
And it's gonna be so fun!

11:43.917 --> 11:46.619
Mr. Radison, who authorized
you to rearrange our study room,

11:46.653 --> 11:48.087
and who do you think
you are anyway?

11:48.122 --> 11:51.157
I'll tell you.

11:52.459 --> 11:53.626
♪ Well ♪

11:53.660 --> 11:55.261
♪ well ♪

11:55.295 --> 11:58.097
♪ well ♪

11:58.132 --> 11:59.999
I'm scared to go
into the study room.

12:00.034 --> 12:01.634
There are so many top hats
in there.

12:01.668 --> 12:03.403
I wish there was a way
